main event: On January 15, 1961, a large fireball was observed traveling from north to south over various locations, including near Minocqua, Wisconsin.
interesting points: Observers noted a strong sulfur odor in the area after the fireball passed., The fireball disintegrated in a burst of greenish light, with fragments shooting in all directions., Multiple witnesses reported seeing the fireball from different angles, indicating a possible path of the object., Some witnesses described the fireball as resembling a burning plane or a large star., There were reports of a humming sound and radio interference in vehicles as the fireball passed overhead.
sighted object: a large fireball emitting light and possibly disintegrating
witness description: Local residents and motorists noted the appearance and behavior of the fireball from various locations.
